theorem Topology.interior_eq_self_of_frontier_disjoint {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (h : frontier A ∩ A = (∅ : Set X)) :
    interior A = A := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · exact interior_subset
  · intro x hxA
    classical
    by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hxInt
    · -- If `x ∉ interior A`, then `x` lies in the frontier of `A`
      have hxFrontier : x ∈ frontier A := by
        have : x ∈ closure A ∧ x ∉ interior A :=
          And.intro (subset_closure hxA) hxInt
        simpa [frontier] using this
      -- Hence `x ∈ frontier A ∩ A`, contradicting the hypothesis `h`
      have hxIn : x ∈ frontier A ∩ A := And.intro hxFrontier hxA
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [h] using hxIn
      cases this

theorem Topology.closure_idempotent {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (closure A) = closure A := by
  simpa [closure_closure]
